data.name: TolerantPropertySetResultType
desc: specifies the possible failure types when using the com.sun.star.beans.XTolerantMultiPropertySet interface.
It usually matches one of the exception types that may occur when using the com.sun.star.beans.XPropertySet or com.sun.star.beans.XMultiPropertySet interfaces.

items.name: ILLEGAL_ARGUMENT
lines: the value used with the property is not valid.
For example if a com.sun.star.lang.IllegalArgumentException was caught.

items.name: PROPERTY_VETO
lines: the property could not be changed at that time.
For example if a com.sun.star.beans.PropertyVetoException was caught.

items.name: SUCCESS
lines: the property has been successfully set or retrieved.

items.name: UNKNOWN_FAILURE
lines: the operation failed and the reason is not known.

items.name: UNKNOWN_PROPERTY
lines: For example if a com.sun.star.beans.UnknownPropertyException was caught.
